<subSubSection id="40B26541FFA1EA026EE0D417FE5FFBA3" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="1091" pageId="3" pageNumber="1089" type="description">
<paragraph id="081736CAFFA1EA026EE0D417FE5FFBA3" blockId="3.[707,1194,433,1729]" lastBlockId="5.[173,660,802,1567]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="1091" pageId="3" pageNumber="1089">
<emphasis id="3ADCEAD8FFA1EA046EE0D417FCEEFDB3" bold="true" box="[731,853,566,587]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1089">Description.</emphasis>
Length 
<quantity id="CF509B2FFFA1EA046F8FD417FBBFFDB3" box="[948,1028,566,587]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.1" pageId="3" pageNumber="1089" unit="mm" value="3.1">3.1 mm</quantity>
from vertex of head to tip of elytra. 
<emphasis id="3ADCEAD8FFA1EA046FA7D470FC61FD9E" bold="true" box="[924,986,593,614]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1089">Head:</emphasis>
Ground color of integument orange except black area on vertex; mandibles darkened apically (
<figureCitation id="90932A4FFFA1EA046F8BD4A7FC41FD63" box="[944,1018,646,667]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[175,206,1658,1677]" captionTargetBox="[166,1157,196,1640]" captionTargetId="figure-1@4.[164,1159,194,1642]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 2. Brodskyella viraktamathi, holotype. A) Habitus, dorsal and lateral views, respectively, C) Head, frontal view, D) Maxillary palpus, E) Antenna, F) Pronotum and head, dorsal view, G) Head and thorax, lateral view, H) Left hind leg, I) Pygidium." pageId="3" pageNumber="1089">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
). Head covered by short, dense, recumbent setae. Eyes comparatively small (ocular index 55.4), reaching occiput, not extending to ventral surface of head, finely facetted (
<figureCitation id="90932A4FFFA1EA046EF1D4D1FC8CFCFD" box="[714,823,752,774]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[175,206,1658,1677]" captionTargetBox="[166,1157,196,1640]" captionTargetId="figure-1@4.[164,1159,194,1642]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 2. Brodskyella viraktamathi, holotype. A) Habitus, dorsal and lateral views, respectively, C) Head, frontal view, D) Maxillary palpus, E) Antenna, F) Pronotum and head, dorsal view, G) Head and thorax, lateral view, H) Left hind leg, I) Pygidium." pageId="3" pageNumber="1089">Fig. 2C–G</figureCitation>
). Maxillary palpi orange, apical palpomere securiform (
<figureCitation id="90932A4FFFA1EA046FB1D52AFC62FCD8" box="[906,985,779,800]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[175,206,1658,1677]" captionTargetBox="[166,1157,196,1640]" captionTargetId="figure-1@4.[164,1159,194,1642]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 2. Brodskyella viraktamathi, holotype. A) Habitus, dorsal and lateral views, respectively, C) Head, frontal view, D) Maxillary palpus, E) Antenna, F) Pronotum and head, dorsal view, G) Head and thorax, lateral view, H) Left hind leg, I) Pygidium." pageId="3" pageNumber="1089">Fig. 2D</figureCitation>
), labial palpi orange, apical palpomere ellipsoidal. Mouthparts lacking any visible sexual dimorphism. Antennae moderately long; antennomeres 1–4 cylindrical; antennomere 1 2.4X longer than wide; antennomere 2 2.0X longer than wide; antennomeres 3–4 2.3X longer than wide; antennomeres 5–10 weakly serrate, 1.6X longer than wide, weakly serrate; all antennomeres bright orange; antennomere 11 ellipsoidal, 2.3X longer than wide (
<figureCitation id="90932A4FFFA1EA046FA2D5DBFC64FBF7" box="[921,991,1018,1039]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[175,206,1658,1677]" captionTargetBox="[166,1157,196,1640]" captionTargetId="figure-1@4.[164,1159,194,1642]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 2. Brodskyella viraktamathi, holotype. A) Habitus, dorsal and lateral views, respectively, C) Head, frontal view, D) Maxillary palpus, E) Antenna, F) Pronotum and head, dorsal view, G) Head and thorax, lateral view, H) Left hind leg, I) Pygidium." pageId="3" pageNumber="1089">Fig. 2E</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="3ADCEAD8FFA1EA046FD6D5DBFB84FBF7" bold="true" box="[1005,1087,1018,1039]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1089">Thorax:</emphasis>
Elytra long and slender, 3.0X as long as wide across humeral calli; ground color of integument orange, becoming dark brown towards elytral margins and suture (
<figureCitation id="90932A4FFFA1EA046EF2D245FCA9FB81" box="[713,786,1124,1145]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[175,206,1658,1677]" captionTargetBox="[166,1157,196,1640]" captionTargetId="figure-1@4.[164,1159,194,1642]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 2. Brodskyella viraktamathi, holotype. A) Habitus, dorsal and lateral views, respectively, C) Head, frontal view, D) Maxillary palpus, E) Antenna, F) Pronotum and head, dorsal view, G) Head and thorax, lateral view, H) Left hind leg, I) Pygidium." pageId="3" pageNumber="1089">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
). Elytra entirely covered by short, recumbent, posteriorly oriented, black setae. Integument of pronotum orange in anterior half and along lateral margins; posteriorly expanded, semitriangular black area present in posterior half of pronotum (
<figureCitation id="90932A4FFFA1EA04686CD2EFFB24FB1B" box="[1111,1183,1230,1251]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[175,206,1658,1677]" captionTargetBox="[166,1157,196,1640]" captionTargetId="figure-1@4.[164,1159,194,1642]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 2. Brodskyella viraktamathi, holotype. A) Habitus, dorsal and lateral views, respectively, C) Head, frontal view, D) Maxillary palpus, E) Antenna, F) Pronotum and head, dorsal view, G) Head and thorax, lateral view, H) Left hind leg, I) Pygidium." pageId="3" pageNumber="1089">Fig. 2F</figureCitation>
). Surface covered by posteriorly oriented, yellowish pubescence. Pronotum subrectangular in dorsal view, 1.2X as long as wide (
<figureCitation id="90932A4FFFA1EA046FCCD33FFBFCFACB" box="[1015,1095,1310,1331]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[175,206,1658,1677]" captionTargetBox="[166,1157,196,1640]" captionTargetId="figure-1@4.[164,1159,194,1642]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 2. Brodskyella viraktamathi, holotype. A) Habitus, dorsal and lateral views, respectively, C) Head, frontal view, D) Maxillary palpus, E) Antenna, F) Pronotum and head, dorsal view, G) Head and thorax, lateral view, H) Left hind leg, I) Pygidium." pageId="3" pageNumber="1089">Fig. 2F</figureCitation>
); anterior margin of pronotum margined, gently curved from median anterior lobe to anterior angles (not visible from above); lateral margin gradually curved, feebly sinuate in lateral aspect; posterior margin emarginate with posterior median lobe protruding backwards; posterior angles obtuse. Ground color of meso- and metathoraces black except reddish brown metacoxal plates; entire integument covered by sparse light yellowish pubescence (
<figureCitation id="90932A4FFFA1EA046F89D02CFBBDF9DA" box="[946,1030,1549,1570]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[175,206,1658,1677]" captionTargetBox="[166,1157,196,1640]" captionTargetId="figure-1@4.[164,1159,194,1642]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 2. Brodskyella viraktamathi, holotype. A) Habitus, dorsal and lateral views, respectively, C) Head, frontal view, D) Maxillary palpus, E) Antenna, F) Pronotum and head, dorsal view, G) Head and thorax, lateral view, H) Left hind leg, I) Pygidium." pageId="3" pageNumber="1089">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
). Scutellum triangular, black. 
<emphasis id="3ADCEAD8FFA1EA046F5DD009FC1BF9C5" bold="true" box="[870,928,1576,1597]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1089">Legs:</emphasis>
Fore legs bright orange; middle and hind legs reddish brown, gradually darkened apically. Protibia straight; protarsus 0.9X longer than protibia. Mesotibia straight; mesotarsus 0.9X longer than mesotibia. Metatibia with 1 apical ridge and 2 oblique lateral ridges. Metatarsomere 1 with 2 ridges, metatarsomeres 2 and 3 each with 1 ridge. Tibial spurs subequal in length, yellow (
<figureCitation id="90932A4FFFA7EA026C8FD576FEBAFC94" box="[180,257,855,876]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[175,206,1658,1677]" captionTargetBox="[166,1157,196,1640]" captionTargetId="figure-1@4.[164,1159,194,1642]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 2. Brodskyella viraktamathi, holotype. A) Habitus, dorsal and lateral views, respectively, C) Head, frontal view, D) Maxillary palpus, E) Antenna, F) Pronotum and head, dorsal view, G) Head and thorax, lateral view, H) Left hind leg, I) Pygidium." pageId="5" pageNumber="1091">Fig. 2H</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="3ADCEAD8FFA7EA026D2AD576FEC7FC94" bold="true" box="[273,380,855,876]" pageId="5" pageNumber="1091">Pygidium:</emphasis>
Conical in dorsal view, 2.7X as long as wide at base (
<figureCitation id="90932A4FFFA7EA026D99D550FE53FC7E" box="[418,488,881,902]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[175,206,1658,1677]" captionTargetBox="[166,1157,196,1640]" captionTargetId="figure-1@4.[164,1159,194,1642]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 2. Brodskyella viraktamathi, holotype. A) Habitus, dorsal and lateral views, respectively, C) Head, frontal view, D) Maxillary palpus, E) Antenna, F) Pronotum and head, dorsal view, G) Head and thorax, lateral view, H) Left hind leg, I) Pygidium." pageId="5" pageNumber="1091">Fig. 2I</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="3ADCEAD8FFA7EA026DC7D550FDD8FC7E" bold="true" box="[508,611,881,902]" pageId="5" pageNumber="1091">Genitalia:</emphasis>
Parameres asymmetrical (
<figureCitation id="90932A4FFFA7EA026DABD5ADFE5AFC59" box="[400,481,908,929]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[197,228,684,703]" captionTargetBox="[176,1188,198,666]" captionTargetId="figure-458@5.[175,1190,194,669]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 3. Brodskyella species, parameres. A) B. konvickai, B) B. viraktmathi, C) B. angustata, D) B. holzschuhi. Illustrations C and B from Horák (1989)." pageId="5" pageNumber="1091">Fig. 3B</figureCitation>
). Right paramere U-shaped; dorsal branch apically expanded and rounded; ventral branch apically narrowed, pointed; ventral branch not overlapping dorsal branch in medial view. Left paramere lacking ventral branch; dorsal branch apically expanded and rounded, covered setae; medial process apically expanded, ventrally produced, truncate at apex.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
