.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="40B26541FFA7EA026CFED2EAFF4CF9E7" pageId="5" pageNumber="1091" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="081736CAFFA7EA026CFED2EAFF4CF9E7" blockId="5.[173,660,802,1567]" pageId="5" pageNumber="1091">
<emphasis id="3ADCEAD8FFA7EA026CFED2EAFE97FB18" bold="true" box="[197,300,1227,1248]" pageId="5" pageNumber="1091">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="CFA84D49FFA7EA026D0FD2EBFD9DFB18" box="[308,550,1226,1248]" class="Insecta" family="Mordellidae" genus="Brodskyella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="1091" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viraktamathi">
<emphasis id="3ADCEAD8FFA7EA026D0FD2EBFD9DFB18" box="[308,550,1226,1248]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="1091">Brodskyella viraktamathi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
closely resembles 
<taxonomicName id="CFA84D49FFA7EA026D3FD2C4FE31FB03" authorityName="Horak" authorityYear="1989" box="[260,394,1253,1275]" class="Insecta" family="Mordellidae" genus="Brodskyella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="1091" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="holzschuhi">
<emphasis id="3ADCEAD8FFA7EA026D3FD2C4FE31FB03" box="[260,394,1253,1275]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="1091">B. holzschuhi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in general appearance but differs from it in having the lateral portions of the pronotum entirely orange instead of orange only in the anterior half in 
<taxonomicName id="CFA84D49FFA7EA026DA4D314FD91FAB2" authorityName="Horak" authorityYear="1989" box="[415,554,1332,1354]" class="Insecta" family="Mordellidae" genus="Brodskyella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="1091" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="holzschuhi">
<emphasis id="3ADCEAD8FFA7EA026DA4D314FD91FAB2" box="[415,554,1332,1354]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="1091">B. holzschuhi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The two species can be reliably separated only by the shape of the parameres (
<figureCitation id="90932A4FFFA7EA026D9ED34BFDAFFA87" box="[421,532,1386,1408]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[197,228,684,703]" captionTargetBox="[176,1188,198,666]" captionTargetId="figure-458@5.[175,1190,194,669]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 3. Brodskyella species, parameres. A) B. konvickai, B) B. viraktmathi, C) B. angustata, D) B. holzschuhi. Illustrations C and B from Horák (1989)." pageId="5" pageNumber="1091">Fig. 3B–D</figureCitation>
): the ventral branch of the right paramere in 
<taxonomicName id="CFA84D49FFA7EA026DD8D3A4FDC6FA62" box="[483,637,1412,1434]" class="Insecta" family="Mordellidae" genus="Brodskyella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="1091" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viraktamathi">
<emphasis id="3ADCEAD8FFA7EA026DD8D3A4FDC6FA62" box="[483,637,1412,1434]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="1091">B. viraktamathi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is strongly curved and is subequal in length to the dorsal branch, whereas in 
<taxonomicName id="CFA84D49FFA7EA026DEDD39BFDDEFA37" authorityName="Horak" authorityYear="1989" box="[470,613,1465,1487]" class="Insecta" family="Mordellidae" genus="Brodskyella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="1091" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="holzschuhi">
<emphasis id="3ADCEAD8FFA7EA026DEDD39BFDDEFA37" box="[470,613,1465,1487]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="1091">B. holzschuhi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the ventral branch is elongate and only moderately curved and is significantly shorter than the dorsal branch.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
